      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Modern historians often view the UN's 21st-century performance as a mixed bag, leaning toward qualified success. While it hasn't prevented major interstate wars on the scale of the 20th century, it has been crucial in mediating conflicts and preventing regional flare-ups from escalating into global conflicts. Its effectiveness is often measured not by stopping wars entirely, but by its ability to manage crises, enforce peacekeeping missions, and provide humanitarian aid. Therefore, the consensus is that it remains a necessary, albeit imperfect, global stabilizer.",
